title: Jo Jorgensen
added: Jorgensen opposes government [[Face masks during the COVID-19 pandemic in the United States#Mask use and policies by state|mask mandates]], considering wearing a face mask to be a matter of personal choice. She argues, though, that mask-wearing would be widely adopted without government intervention because [[market competition]] would drive businesses to adopt either mask-required or mask-optional policies, allowing consumers the [[freedom to choose]] their preferred environment. Jorgensen has invoked the analogy of [[dollar voting]] to explain how consumer preferences would shape businesses' policies on face masks in the absence of a government mandate.<ref name="Reason interview">{{cite news |last1=Gillespie |first1=Nick |authorlink1=Nick Gillespie |title=Jo Jorgensen: Don't Waste Your Vote on Trump or Biden |url=https://reason.com/podcast/jo-jorgensen-dont-waste-your-vote-on-trump-or-biden/ |accessdate=30 September 2020 |agency=Reason |date=23 September 2020 |location=21:48–29:00 |format=interview}}</ref>
